data.value: In the city where the independence movement begins, North End, known as “Little Italy”, is preferred as well as Quincy Market and Faneuil Hall for food, drink and socialization. Serving since 1969, The New England Aquarium does not only give you the opportunity to know sea creatures, but also organizes whale watching trips. The Freedom Road in the city center gives you the opportunity to see 16 historical buildings. A. Again.B.Those who want to know history of D can see the Boston Tea Party Museum and Naval Museum. Harvard University, one of the most famous and prestigious schools in the world, is located in Boston.
